CHANGES FROM VERSION 2.16.1

* Applied patches for ipv6 support, contributed by Samuel Thibault.
  (Note that, due to a bug in OCaml 3.08.3, this code will not
  actually work with ipv6 unless compiled with the CVS version of the
  OCaml compiler, where the bug has been fixed; however, ipv4 should
  continue to work normally.)

-------------------------------
CHANGES FROM VERSION 2.16.-2

* Bumped version number to 2.16.  (Everybody doing committs should
  remember to do this manually whenever the wire protocol changes,
  e.g. when preferences are added...)

-------------------------------
CHANGES FROM VERSION 2.15.6

* Fix to the Mac command-line tool.

-------------------------------
CHANGES FROM VERSION 2.15.5

Added a few sentences to the documentation of the new merging stuff.

I think this stuff (the new merge implementation as well as, more
importantly, the new implementation of backups) is now just about
ready to be used by others.  In fact, it would be useful to have a few
more people try it to flush out any remaining bugs.  

Please keep a careful eye on what it is doing, though, if you choose
to upgrade.



-------------------------------
CHANGES FROM VERSION 2.15.1

* Couple more tweaks to the merging function.  I can run Unison together with Harmony now, it seems.

-------------------------------
CHANGES FROM VERSION 2.15.0

* More work on merging functionality -- fixed one nasty bug in the
  code that updates the archive, but merging is still not completely
  working.



